description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse Band 5 – Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Coronary Care Unit &amp; Cardiology Ward Basingstoke&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description: &lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking enthusiastic nurses to work within our Cardiac Wards. You will be supported by our caring and passionate team to manage critically unwell patients and those with chronic cardiac conditions. Learning from our experienced team as you develop practical skills and knowledge including : ECG recognition and care of patient’s pre and post angiographic and pacing procedures from our Cardiac Cath Lab. We welcome applications from newly qualified nurses and those with experience looking for new challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to learn and develop new knowledge and skills in a well supported environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work in an often fast paced environment, staying calm and focused, ready to respond in emergency situations and working with the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion to deliver high quality care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with an experienced and knowledgeable Cardiology Team where you will be encouraged and supported to learn and expand clinical skills and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to experience shifts in our Cardiac Cath Lab to further develop your knowledge and skills and inform your patient care and education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop leadership skills to allow you to support the Nurse in Charge and progress your personal develop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the Trust are happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiac Care Unit consists of a 15 bedded Coronary Care Unit with a 4 bedded Cardiac Assessment Unit plus 12 Cardiology step down beds. The unit is adjacent to our Cardiac Cath Lab which provides 24/7 direct access via Ambulance and ED for Primary PCI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will experience caring for patients pre and post Coronary Angiography, Angioplasty, Permanent Pace Makers, Complex Devices and Internal Defibrillators. Preparing and supporting patients for surgical procedures. Working with our team caring for our Heart Failure Patients and medical patients with Cardiac needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vision at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to provide outstanding care for every patient. We serve a population of nearly 600,000 people across Hampshire and West Berkshire as well as some people who access our specialist services from across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created in January 2012 the Foundation Trust prioritises the provision of exceptional, compassionate, care delivered by the valued staff working in a culture of collaboration and mutual respect. HHFT employs circa 6,000 people and had a turnover of £382m in 17/18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Four core values (CARE) Compassion, Accountability, Respect and Encourage. These are in place to support of four clear objectives, provide outstanding care of patients, empowering all members of staff, sustainable growth and innovating for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; #AspringToBeTheBest &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
